    >
      <h2>1. Thesis</h2>
      <p>
        The defining reality of GEO in mid-2026: there is no single "AI citation" game. Five platforms draw from
        different webs, sharing as little as <a
          href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-11-percent-ai-citation-overlap">11% of cited domains</a
        >. Yet beneath the divergence, every platform converges on entity clarity, structural evidence, and continuous
        brand footprint expansion. The old question was "how do I rank for this keyword?" The new question is "does
        every major AI platform know who I am — and can they prove it from my content?"
      </p>

      <h2>2. The State Now</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/basics#entry-ai-overviews-86-percent-us-searches"
          >AI Overviews appear on 86.7% of US searches</a
        >
        (commercial-intent 88.5%), reaching 2.5B monthly users versus ~800M for ChatGPT. Google shipped a dedicated AI visibility
        report in Search Console showing impressions (no clicks, no CTR, no query-level data), and stated that
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-google-search-console-ai-visibility-report"
          >AIO optimization is SEO for Google specifically</a
        >. Content with author attribution is
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-google-ai-overviews-author-name-bio-required"
          >4x more likely to be cited</a
        >, and the freshness window was cut from 365 to 180 days.
      </p>
      <p>But aggregating platforms conceals more than it reveals.</p>
      <p>
        <strong>ChatGPT</strong> has the narrowest aperture: it cites the vendor's own site
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-chatgpt-first-party-site-68-percent-citations"
          >68% of the time</a
        >, relies on
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-chatgpt-wikipedia-29-percent-dependency"
          >Wikipedia for 29.7% of its top cited pages</a
        >
        and brand homepages for 23.8%. ChatGPT largely deprioritizes video, community discussion, and personal blogs — though
        community platforms account for 52.5% of citations industry-wide. Citation follows steep position decay — the top
        retrieval result is cited
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-chatgpt-position-citation-decay-58-14">58% of the time</a>,
        position 10 only 14%.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Perplexity</strong> is the opposite:
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-perplexity-46-percent-reddit-sources"
          >24% niche-site citation rate</a
        >
        (2–3x ChatGPT), aggressive freshness premium — content updated within 30 days earns
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-perplexity-freshness-premium-45-points"
          >82% citation rate vs 37% for content over a year old</a
        >, a 45-point advantage. Perplexity responds to new content in
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-perplexity-freshness-premium-45-points">5–7 days</a> vs 3–5 weeks
        for ChatGPT. It draws
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-perplexity-46-percent-reddit-sources"
          >46.7% of its top-10 sources from Reddit</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Claude</strong> biases toward premium editorial — citing the New York Times, the Atlantic, and the New Yorker
        at roughly
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-claude-premium-editorial-bias"
          >2x the rate of other platforms</a
        >. It has the longest freshness window: 3x more likely than ChatGPT to cite content 2–4 weeks old. Claude's AI
        visibility
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-previsible-claude-64x-growth">grew 64x</a>
        over the tracking period, overtaking Perplexity.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Gemini</strong> is the most schema-responsive and conservative engine, citing brand-owned sites at
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-gemini-schema-responsive-52-percent-owned">52%</a>
        — the highest rate of any platform. Gemini is the fastest-growing, having
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-b2b-saas-dominates-ai-citations-34-percent"
          >doubled month-over-month</a
        >. Critically, it shares only
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-gemini-schema-responsive-52-percent-owned"
          >13.7% of its citations with Google's own AI Overviews</a
        >
        on identical queries. The Gemini 3 model update collapsed the AI Overview–organic top-10 overlap from
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-gemini-3-collapsed-top-10-overlap">76% to 38%</a>. Fan-out
        sub-query mapping is now the dominant mechanism.
      </p>
      <p>
        Across all platforms, the median cited-source half-life is approximately
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-ai-citation-half-life-4-5-weeks">4.5 weeks</a>. 40–60% of
        cited domains rotate month-to-month. Content &lt;13 weeks old is about
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-content-freshness-13-week-shelf-life"
          >2x more likely to be cited</a
        >, though a controlled Ahrefs study of 16.975M URLs shows the actual freshness advantage is
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-content-freshness-25-percent-advantage">25.7%</a>
        — not the unsourced 4.3x figure.
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-community-platforms-52-percent-citations"
          >Community platforms</a
        >
        capture 52.5% of all AI citations versus 47.5% from brand domains. Top-3 Google pages are
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-seo-floor-top-3-pages-34x-cited"
          >34x more likely to be cited by AI</a
        >
        than pages ranked 31–100 (114,034 observations), confirming that traditional SEO ranking gates AI visibility.
      </p>
      <p>
        Google's AI Overviews now trigger on
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-google-ai-overviews-48-percent-ctr-drop-61"
          >48% of queries</a
        >
        (healthcare 88%, education 83%, B2B tech 82%). On queries with AIOs, organic CTR drops 61%; even queries without AIOs
        saw a 41% CTR decline.
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-ai-search-converts-4-4x-better-than-organic"
          >83% of AI Overview citations come from outside the organic top 10</a
        >. Being cited is now the primary CTR preservation strategy.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-ai-error-monitoring-67-days-unmonitored"
          >Unmonitored brands take 67 days to detect AI citation errors</a
        >
        vs 14 days for monitored ones. Error rates: e-commerce 18%, SaaS 12%, finance 11.3%.
      </p>
      <p>
        The economics are stark: AI traffic converts at a
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-platform-specific-citation-conversion-rates"
          >14.2% average</a
        >
        vs Google organic's 2.8% — 4.4x — with platform spreads (Claude 16.8%, ChatGPT 14.2%, Perplexity 12.4%). Brands cited
        in AI Overviews see
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-cited-brand-premium-35-91-ctr"
          >+35% higher organic CTR and +91% higher paid CTR</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The schema paradox:</strong> One study shows
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-schema-markup-2-3x-citation-lift">2.3x citation lift</a>
        from FAQPage, HowTo, Article, and Product schema. Another tracked 1,885 pages adding schema vs 4,000 controls and
        found
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-schema-markup-near-zero-independent-effect"
          >zero meaningful lift</a
        >. Both are valid: schema does not independently <em>cause</em> citation — authoritative sites use both schema and
        quality content. But attribute-rich Product/Review schema with populated ratings outperforms generic by
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-attribute-rich-schema-20pp-citation-lift"
          >20pp (61.7% vs 41.6%)</a
        >.
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-faq-rich-results-deprecated-signal-remains"
          >FAQPage was deprecated for rich result display in May 2026</a
        >, but the AI citation extraction signal remains active. Comparison tables deliver
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-comparison-tables-llm-txt-faq-schema-lift">+34%</a>,
        llm.txt +32%, and FAQ schema +28% coverage lift within 14–21 days.
      </p>

      <h2>3. What's Winning</h2>
      <p>The strongest verified signals all prove a brand exists independently of its own website.</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Entity signals dominate.</strong> The SEO-to-GEO Divergence Index shows Brand Entity Mentions at NIS 0.918
        versus Domain Rating at
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-brand-entity-mentions-surpass-domain-rating">NIS 0.397</a>
        — entity signals are more than twice as predictive as link authority. Across 75,000 brands, branded web mentions correlate
        at
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-brand-mentions-3x-stronger-than-backlinks"
          >r=0.664 vs backlinks r=0.218</a
        >
        — a 3x gap. The top quartile averages 169 AI Overview mentions; the next tier manages just 14. The
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-brand-stature-ladder-73-44-11-percent"
          >Brand Stature Ladder</a
        >
        shows global brands at 73% citation rate, mid-market 44%, niche 11%.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Review depth</strong> is the single highest-correlated variable:
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-review-depth-strongest-geo-predictor"
          >50+ reviews on G2/Capterra = 3.2x citation rate</a
        >. <strong>Wikidata QID with sameAs schema</strong> lifts citation rates by
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-wikidata-qid-entity-seo-signal-40-percent"
          >40% with zero ongoing cost</a
        >. Google's
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-google-llm-patent-teaching-ai-who-you-are">LLM patent</a>
        confirms the SEO goal is teaching AI who you are. <strong>Third-party sources</strong> account for
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-third-party-sources-68-percent-citations"
          >68% of AI citations</a
        >; one source = 18% lift, five or more = 78%.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Content signals:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-quotation-addition-strongest-geo-tactic"
            >Named-source quotations with credentials</a
          >: +42.6% citation lift (strongest Princeton GEO tactic)
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-data-rich-content-19-stats-5x-citations"
            >19+ data points per page</a
          >: 5.4 citations vs 2.8, nearly double. Statistics + sources boost visibility 40%
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-answer-first-content-architecture"
            >Answer-first architecture</a
          >: direct answer in first 1–3 sentences.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-llm-citations-44-percent-front-loaded"
            >44.2% of LLM citations</a
          >
          come from the first 30% of text; claim-rich introductions get cited 2.1x more
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-multi-format-content-2-3x-citations">Multi-format content</a
          >: guides + comparisons + how-to = 2.3x citation rate
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/basics#entry-original-datasets-highest-roi-tactic">Original datasets</a>:
          highest-ROI GEO tactic — AI cannot synthesize data it lacks access to
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-topic-targeting-replaces-keyword-targeting"
            >Topic targeting</a
          >
          replaces keyword targeting
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Case study validation:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          B2B SaaS
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-87-percent-citation-rate-reviews-pr"
            >12% to 87% citation rate in 4 months</a
          >
          (G2 reviews, 14 PR placements, comparison hubs, schema)
        </li>
        <li>
          Industrial lighting
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-88-percent-ai-recommendation-pr-consensus"
            >88.6% AI recommendation rate</a
          >
          — own site contributed only 4.5% of citations, PR reprints drove 59.8%
        </li>
        <li>
          B2B manufacturing
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-b2b-manufacturing-50-percent-citation-rate"
            >50% citation rate in 112 days without landing pages</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          Fulton
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-fulton-35x-ai-revenue-case-study"
            >from zero to $18,164/month in 12 months</a
          >, 700% revenue increase in 6 weeks, Google organic doubled as side effect
        </li>
        <li>
          Snack brand
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-snack-brand-75-percent-citation-rate-ahe-framework"
            >75% generative citation rate from zero in 4 months</a
          >
          via direct-answer blocks and FAQ/HowTo schema
        </li>
        <li>
          CITABLE framework from
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-citable-framework-b2b-saas-trials"
            >~500 to 3,500+ monthly AI-referred trials</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          The compiled benchmark shows
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-geo-case-study-benchmark-2026"
            >2,300% AI traffic growth</a
          >
          with a 90–180 day inflection point
        </li>
        <li>
          At least one case achieved
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/case-studies#entry-geo-seven-day-visibility-jaeckert-case-study"
            >6.8% to 46.7% in 7 days</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Losing Signals</h2>
      <p>
        The KB currently flags no signals as formally deprecated or stale. But several contested findings and structural
        limitations are worth tracking:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Google self-conflict.</strong> Gemini and AI Overviews share only
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-gemini-schema-responsive-52-percent-owned"
          >13.7% of citations</a
        >
        on identical queries. The AIO–organic overlap collapsed from
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-aio-overlap-organic-collapse-76-to-38">76% to 38%</a>.
        Optimizing for one Google surface does not optimize for another.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The schema paradox persists.</strong> Schema produces
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-schema-markup-2-3x-citation-lift"
          >2.3x lift in one study</a
        >
        and
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-schema-markup-near-zero-independent-effect"
          >zero independent effect in another</a
        >. The difference is methodological — observational vs controlled — and the resolution is that schema amplifies
        quality but does not create it.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Freshness is real but overclaimed.</strong> The controlled advantage is
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-content-freshness-25-percent-advantage">25.7%</a>, not the
        viral 4.3x figure. But the ~4.5-week half-life means continuity is still mandatory — the penalty for staleness
        is persistent churn, not a multiplier.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Only 36 brands</strong> maintain top-100 visibility across ChatGPT, Gemini, AI Mode, and AI Overviews simultaneously
        (<a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-semrush-universal-36-brands">Semrush 126M prompts</a>).
        Those outside this set face structural disadvantages that no single content fix resolves.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hallucination trajectories diverge.</strong>
        <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-gpt-5-citation-hallucination-halved"
          >GPT-5-mini hallucinates at 11.4%</a
        >, down from GPT-4o-mini's 45.3%, but Claude Haiku 4.5 increased 8%. Multi-model consensus achieves 95.6%
        accuracy, but relying on any single platform carries citation integrity risk.
      </p>

      <h2>5. What Changed This Cycle</h2>
      <p>
        This is the inaugural edition of the State of GEO living document. Every entry in the delta is marked as new
        because there is no prior snapshot to compare against. The document is built from 67 initial knowledge base
        entries spanning measurement, content, entity SEO, schema markup, technical infrastructure, case studies, and
        monetization, collected through July 2026. Future editions will show additions, updates, and removals.
      </p>

      <h2>6. What To Do</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Audit per platform, not aggregate.</strong> Use
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/tools#entry-gsc-ai-mode-segmentation"
            >GSC's AI Mode and AI Overviews segmentation</a
          >. Add dedicated tools for ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-ai-overviews-brand-citation-rates"
            >AIO brands cited at 59.8%</a
          >
          vs ChatGPT 44.7% and Perplexity 28.9% — different platforms, different levers.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-b2b-saas-dominates-ai-citations-34-percent"
            >B2B SaaS dominates at 34% of tracked citations</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Build the entity foundation first.</strong> Wikidata entry + sameAs Organization schema. Zero-cost intervention,
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-wikidata-qid-entity-seo-signal-40-percent"
            >40% citation lift</a
          >. Brands with Wikipedia earn
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/entity-seo#entry-chatgpt-wikipedia-29-percent-dependency"
            >3x higher citation rates</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Shift link budget to mention budget.</strong>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-brand-mentions-3x-stronger-than-backlinks"
            >Brand mentions are 3x stronger than backlinks</a
          >. PR placements, G2/Trustpilot reviews, Reddit community. One firm used
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/technical#entry-llms-txt-ai-discovery-files-competitive"
            >AI Discovery Files</a
          >
          to score 99/100 against national brands — structured facts over backlinks.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Restructure for passage-level extraction.</strong> Every H2 needs a direct answer block in the first 40–60
          words.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-document-structure-17-percent-citation-lift"
            >44.9% of citation improvement comes from macro-structure</a
          >. The
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-gainframe-playbook-31-percent-chatgpt">GainFrame playbook</a>
          — Quick Answer blocks, question H2s, FAQ schema, IndexNow — made ChatGPT the top acquisition channel at 31%.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Adopt monthly publication cycles.</strong>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/content#entry-content-freshness-13-week-shelf-life"
            >Content &lt;13 weeks is ~2x more likely to be cited</a
          >. Perplexity rewards days-old content; ChatGPT responds in 3–5 weeks.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/schema-markup#entry-comparison-tables-llm-txt-faq-schema-lift"
            >Comparison tables +34%, llm.txt +32%, FAQ schema +28%</a
          >
          coverage lift within 14–21 days.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Audit AI crawler access — hard deadline Sep 15, 2026.</strong>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/technical#entry-73-percent-websites-block-ai-crawlers"
            >73% of websites block AI crawlers</a
          >.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/technical#entry-js-rendered-content-77-percent-fail"
            >JS-rendered content fails 77% of parser attempts</a
          >.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/technical#entry-cloudflare-three-tier-crawler-classification"
            >Cloudflare's three-tier classification</a
          >
          blocks Training and Agent crawlers by default on ad-supported pages. Unlike the monthly content cadence, this is
          a one-off with a fixed date.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Deploy AI Discovery Files.</strong> llms.txt, llms-full.txt, and robots.txt allowances for all three Cloudflare
          crawler tiers as needed.
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-gpt-5-citation-hallucination-halved"
            >GPT-5's reduced hallucination</a
          >
          makes well-structured content more likely to be cited accurately.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Budget for continuity, not campaigns.</strong>
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/monetization#entry-b2b-geo-budget-guide-35-60k">$35–60K/year</a>, 15–30% of
          marketing budget, 12–18 month payback. The
          <a href="https://citonyx.com/learn/measurement#entry-ai-citation-half-life-4-5-weeks">4.5-week half-life</a>
          means GEO is a continuity discipline — once you stop investing, the citations rotate out within weeks.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>7. Method Note</h2>
      <p>
        This is the inaugural edition of the State of GEO, a living document synthesized from 67 curated findings in the
        Citonyx knowledge base. Sources include peer-reviewed studies (arXiv, ACL 2026), independent audits (Ahrefs,
        Semrush, Averi, Profound, Yext, OtterlyAI, BrightEdge, SE Ranking, Ranqo, AirOps, Erlin, Foglift, Peec AI,
        Previsible, Passionfruit, Hebbia), platform data, and documented case studies. Each factual claim links to its
        source entry for independent verification. The synthesis and analytical conclusions are the author's. The
        underlying studies are predominantly English-language and US-centric. Given the ~4.5-week citation half-life,
        treat this as a July 2026 snapshot. Updated every two weeks.
      </p>
